How to Download Git:
Go to "https://git-scm.com/".
Click **Windows**.
Click **Click here to download**.
After the download is completed, open the Git setup file on the laptop.
Click **Next** for all the questions and finally click **Finish**.

Open Command Prompt in laptop.
Enter the command: git
Example:
C:\Users\ekiruba>git
Note : If Git is installed correctly, Git information will appear, which means Git is set up on the computer.

Set Username and Email ID in Git:
Enter the command : git config --global user.name "{{GitHub user name}}"
Example : C:\Users\ekiruba>git config --global user.name "Kiruba"

Enter the command : git config --global user.email "{{GitHub login email}}"
Example : C:\Users\ekiruba>git config --global user.email "kirubaelango03@gmail.com"

Now Git setup is ready for working, so close the Command Prompt.

Download Visual studio code : 
Go to "https://code.visualstudio.com/"
